headline.print_headline: News Guide: Eating Right Still at Core of Dietary Guidelines
headline.main: News Guide: Eating Right Still at Core of Dietary Guidelines

docs.lead_paragraph: Dietary advice can be confusing. Is it OK to eat meat and eggs? Is fat in or out? What about grains? How much salt?

headline.print_headline: Mississippi, West Virginia Toughest on School Immunizations
headline.main: Mississippi, West Virginia Toughest on School Immunizations

docs.lead_paragraph: With rampant diabetes and obesity, Mississippi and West Virginia have struggled with health crises. Yet when it comes to getting children vaccinated, these states don't mess around.

headline.print_headline: Puerto Rico Considers Fining Parents of Obese Children
headline.main: Puerto Rico Considers Fining Parents of Obese Children

docs.lead_paragraph: Legislators in Puerto Rico are debating a bill that would fine parents of obese children up to $800 if they don't lose weight.

headline.print_headline: The Fat Fight: Study Fuels Row Over UK, U.S. Diet Guidelines
headline.main: The Fat Fight: Study Fuels Row Over UK, U.S. Diet Guidelines
How to Prioritize and Save Young Lives

docs.lead_paragraph: There’s a disconnect between what we think kills children and what actually does. In the U.S., it makes sense to focus on accidents, homicide and suicide.
